        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer486230094" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6229840803232711294"> Errgh. This book has such great characters and plot. Everything was really well thought out. I especially liked some of the minor characters. Everyone had a story. There were a lot of emotions covered in this book, and it was just really sweet. The only thing I didn&apos;t like, especially at he beginning, was the writing style. But it does get better, or at least you get used to it, one of the two, by the middle of the book, so if the writing really bothers you at the beginning of the book, push th</span>
  <span id="freeText6229840803232711294" style="display:none"> Errgh. This book has such great characters and plot. Everything was really well thought out. I especially liked some of the minor characters. Everyone had a story. There were a lot of emotions covered in this book, and it was just really sweet. The only thing I didn't like, especially at he beginning, was the writing style. But it does get better, or at least you get used to it, one of the two, by the middle of the book, so if the writing really bothers you at the beginning of the book, push through because it's worth it. Oh also, it is told in duel perspectives between Alex and his brother James, which I guess is just a personal preference, but I loved that aspect, and it was done really well. Mmmm ya, good stuff.</span>
